    <title>The Lefschetz properties of monomial complete intersections in positive
  characteristic</title>
    <summary>  Stanley proved that, in characteristic zero, all artinian monomial complete
intersections have the strong Lefschetz property. We provide a positive
characteristic complement to Stanley's result in the case of artinian monomial
complete intersections generated by monomials all of the same degree, and also
for arbitrary artinian monomial complete intersections in characteristic two.
  To establish these results, we first prove an a priori lower bound on the
characteristics that guarantee the Lefschetz properties. We then use a variety
of techniques to complete the classifications.
</summary>
